symptoms: Brake pedal feels soft or spongy
brake pedal sticks to the floor

brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
vehicle is unable to stop
grinding noise
pulsating brakes
screeching sound when pushing on the brakes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The design of the brake pedal can cause the driver to accidentally press the accelerator pedal while trying to brake, leading to accidents or loss of control of the vehicle.
symptoms: Brake pedal is too close to the accelerator pedal

vehicle surges forward unexpectedly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of airbags to deploy in the event of a crash can lead to serious injuries or fatalities, as the occupants may not be adequately protected from the impact.
symptoms: Airbags fail to deploy in the event of a crash
despite the severity of the impact; occupants may experience injuries or fatalities as a result.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The recall of Takata airbags can lead to the deployment of faulty airbags, which can cause injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The airbag dash light remains on when the engine is running; the airbag may deploy improperly in the event of a crash.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Sudden acceleration can lead to loss of control of the vehicle, resulting in accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly accelerates to a high speed without warning
making it difficult for the driver to maintain control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries. The failure of the vehicle to respond to braking inputs can lead to increased stopping distances, further increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates without warning
the brake pedal is applied
but the vehicle fails to stop
the engine surges or runs hard
the vehicle lurches forward or backward
the accelerator pedal sticks or feels stuck.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Loss of vehicle control can cause accidents, injuries, and fatalities. The failure of the vehicle to respond to steering inputs can lead to loss of traction, skidding, and rollovers.
symptoms: The vehicle lurches or pulls to one side
the rear of the vehicle loses traction
the vehicle slides or skids
the vehicle overturns or rolls over.
